</td></tr></table></div><div style='margin-left: 5px'>As I noted and linked to above, CDC mortality statistics on gun-linked mortality are easily obtained and detailed. FBI violent crime statistics are also easy to obtain.</div><div style='margin-top: 3px; font-size: smaller'><span class='commentlinks'>(<a href="http://squid314.livejournal.com/347454.html?replyto=3686206" rel="nofollow">Reply</a>) </span>(<a href='http://squid314.livejournal.com/347454.html?thread=3685694#t3685694'>Parent</a>) (<a href='http://squid314.livejournal.com/347454.html?thread=3686206#t3686206'>Thread</a>) <span id='expand_3686206'>(<a href='http://squid314.livejournal.com/347454.html?thread=3686206#t3686206' onclick="ExpanderEx.make(event,this,'http://squid314.livejournal.com/347454.html?thread=3686206#t3686206','3686206',true)">Expand</a>)</span><div class="quickreply" id="ljqrt3686206" style="display: none;"></div></div></div><div style='margin-left: 50px;margin-top:5px;' id="ljcmt3688766">
